==Events== *[[477 BC]] &ndash; [[Battle of the Cremera]] as part of the [[Roman–Etruscan_Wars#The_Fabian_war_with_Veii_in_483-476_BC|Roman–Etruscan Wars]]. [[Veii]] ambushes and defeats the [[Roman Republic|Roman]] army. *[[390 BC]] &ndash; [[Roman Republic|Roman]]-[[Gaulish language|Gaulish]] Wars: [[Battle of the Allia]]: A Roman army is defeated by raiding [[Gauls]], leading to the subsequent sacking of [[Ancient Rome|Rome]]. * [[362]] &ndash; [[Roman–Persian Wars]]: Emperor [[Julian (emperor)|Julian]] arrives at [[Antioch]] with a Roman expeditionary force (60,000 men) and stays there for nine months to launch a campaign against the [[Sasanian Empire|Persian Empire]]. * [[452]] &ndash; [[Sack of Aquileia]]: After an earlier [[Battle of the Catalaunian Plains|defeat on the Catalaunian Plains]], [[Attila]] lays siege to the metropolis of [[Aquileia]] and eventually destroys it. * [[645]] &ndash; Chinese forces under general [[Li Shiji]] besiege the strategic fortress city of [[Anshan|Anshi]] ([[Liaoning]]) during the [[Goguryeo–Tang War]]. *[[1195]] &ndash; [[Battle of Alarcos]]: [[Almohad Caliphate|Almohad]] forces defeat the [[Kingdom of Castile|Castilian]] army of [[Alfonso VIII of Castile|Alfonso VIII]] and force its retreat to [[Toledo, Spain|Toledo]]. *[[1290]] &ndash; King [[Edward I of England]] issues the [[Edict of Expulsion]], banishing all Jews (numbering about 16,000) from England; this was [[Tisha B'Av]] on the [[Hebrew calendar]], a day that commemorates many Jewish calamities. *[[1334]] &ndash; The bishop of [[Florence]] blesses the first foundation stone for the new ''[[Bell tower|campanile]]'' (bell tower) of the [[Florence Cathedral]], designed by the artist [[Giotto|Giotto di Bondone]]. *[[1389]] &ndash; [[Kingdom of France|France]] and [[Kingdom of England|England]] agree to the [[Truce of Leulinghem]], inaugurating a 13-year peace, the longest period of sustained peace during the [[Hundred Years' War]]. *[[1391]] &ndash; [[Tokhtamysh–Timur war]]: [[Battle of the Kondurcha River]]: [[Timur]] defeats [[Tokhtamysh]] of the [[Golden Horde]] in present-day southeast Russia. *[[1555]] &ndash; The [[College of Arms]] is reincorporated by [[Royal charter]] signed by Queen [[Mary I of England]] and King [[Philip II of Spain]]. *[[1806]] &ndash; A [[1806 Birgu polverista explosion|gunpowder magazine explosion]] in [[Birgu]], [[Malta Protectorate|Malta]], kills around 200 people. *[[1812]] &ndash; The [[Treaty of Orebro|Treaties of Orebro]] end both the [[Anglo-Russian War (1807–12)|Anglo-Russian]] and [[Anglo-Swedish War (1810–12)|Anglo-Swedish Wars]]. *[[1841]] &ndash; Coronation of Emperor [[Pedro II of Brazil]]. *[[1857]] &ndash; [[Louis Faidherbe]], French [[governor of Senegal]], arrives to relieve French forces at [[Kayes]], effectively ending El Hajj [[El Hadj Umar Tall|Umar Tall]]'s war against the French. *[[1862]] &ndash; First ascent of [[Dent Blanche]], one of the highest summits in the Alps. *[[1863]] &ndash; [[American Civil War]]: [[Second Battle of Fort Wagner]]: One of the first formal [[African American]] military units, the [[54th Regiment Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry|54th Massachusetts Volunteer Infantry]], supported by several white regiments, attempts an unsuccessful assault on [[Confederate States of America|Confederate]]-held [[Fort Wagner|Battery Wagner]]. *[[1870]] &ndash; The [[First Vatican Council]] decrees the dogma of [[papal infallibility]]. *[[1872]] &ndash; The [[Ballot Act 1872]] in the United Kingdom introduced the requirement that parliamentary and local government elections be held by secret ballot. *[[1914]] &ndash; The [[United States Congress|U.S. Congress]] forms the [[Aviation Section, U.S. Signal Corps]], giving official status to aircraft within the U.S. Army for the first time. *[[1925]] &ndash; [[Adolf Hitler]] publishes ''[[Mein Kampf]]''. *[[1942]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: During the [[Beisfjord massacre]] in Norway, 15 Norwegian paramilitary guards help members of the SS to kill 288 political prisoners from Yugoslavia. * 1942 &ndash; The Germans test fly the [[Messerschmitt Me 262]] using its [[Junkers Jumo 004|jet engine]]s for the first time. *[[1944]] &ndash; World War II: [[Hideki Tōjō]] resigns as [[Prime Minister of Japan]] because of numerous setbacks in the war effort. *[[1966]] &ndash; [[Human spaceflight]]: [[Gemini 10]] is launched from [[Cape Canaveral|Cape Kennedy]] on a 70-hour mission that includes docking with an orbiting [[Agena target vehicle]]. * 1966 &ndash; A racially charged incident in a bar sparks the six-day [[Hough riots]] in [[Cleveland|Cleveland, Ohio]]; 1,700 [[Ohio National Guard]] troops intervene to restore order. *[[1968]] &ndash; [[Intel]] is founded in [[Mountain View, California]]. *[[1969]] &ndash; U.S. Senator [[Ted Kennedy]] crashes his car into a tidal basin at [[Chappaquiddick Island, Massachusetts]], killing his passenger, ''[[Boiler Room Girls|Boiler Room Girl]]'' [[Mary Jo Kopechne]]. *[[1976]] &ndash; [[Nadia Comăneci]] becomes the first person in [[Olympic Games]] history to score a perfect 10 in [[gymnastics]] at the [[1976 Summer Olympics]]. *[[1982]] &ndash; Two hundred sixty-eight [[Guatemala]]n ''campesinos'' ("[[peasant]]s" or "country people") are slain in the [[Plan de Sánchez massacre]]. *[[1984]] &ndash; [[San Ysidro McDonald's massacre|McDonald's massacre]] in [[San Ysidro, San Diego|San Ysidro, California]]: In a fast-food restaurant, James Oliver Huberty opens fire, killing 21 people and injuring 19 others before being shot dead by police. *[[1992]] &ndash; A picture of [[Les Horribles Cernettes]] was taken, which became the first ever photo posted to the [[World Wide Web]]. *[[1994]] &ndash; The [[AMIA bombing|bombing]] of the [[Asociación Mutual Israelita Argentina]] (Argentine Jewish Community Center) in [[Buenos Aires]] kills 85 people (mostly Jewish) and injures 300. * 1994 &ndash; [[Rwandan genocide]]: The [[Rwandan Patriotic Front]] takes control of [[Gisenyi]] and north western [[Rwanda]], forcing the interim government into [[Zaire]] and ending the genocide. *[[1995]] &ndash; On the Caribbean island of [[Montserrat]], the [[Soufrière Hills]] volcano erupts. Over the course of several years, it devastates the island, destroying the capital, forcing most of the population to flee. * [[1996]] &ndash; Storms provoke [[Saguenay flood|severe flooding]] on the [[Saguenay River]], beginning one of [[Quebec]]'s costliest [[natural disaster]]s ever. * 1996 &ndash; [[Battle of Mullaitivu (1996)|Battle of Mullaitivu]]: The [[Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam]] capture the [[Sri Lanka Army]]'s base, killing over 1200 soldiers. *[[2012]] &ndash; At least seven people are killed and 32 others are injured after a [[2012 Burgas bus bombing|bomb explodes]] on an [[Israelis|Israeli]] tour bus at [[Burgas Airport]], [[Bulgaria]]. *[[2013]] &ndash; The [[Government of Detroit]], with up to $20 billion in debt, files for the [[Detroit bankruptcy|largest municipal bankruptcy]] in U.S. history.
