==Events== * [[363]] &ndash; Emperor [[Julian (emperor)|Julian]] marches back up the [[Tigris]] and burns his fleet of supply ships. During the withdrawal Roman forces suffered several attacks from the [[Persia]]ns. * [[632]] &ndash; [[Yazdegerd III]] ascends to the throne as king (''[[shah]]'') of the [[Sasanian Empire|Persian Empire]]. He becomes the last ruler of the [[Sasanian family tree|Sasanian dynasty]] (modern [[Iran]]). *[[1407]] &ndash; [[Ming–Hồ War]]: Retired King [[Hồ Quý Ly]] and his son King [[Hồ Hán Thương]] of [[Hồ dynasty]] are captured by the [[Ming dynasty|Ming]] armies. *[[1487]] &ndash; [[Battle of Stoke Field]], the final engagement of the [[Wars of the Roses]]. *[[1586]] &ndash; [[Mary, Queen of Scots]], recognizes [[Philip II of Spain]] as her [[Order of succession#Monarchies and nobility|heir and successor]]. *[[1745]] &ndash; [[War of the Austrian Succession]]: [[New England]] colonial troops under the command of [[William Pepperrell]] capture the [[Fortress of Louisbourg]] in [[Louisbourg]], [[New France]] ([[Old Style]] date). *[[1746]] &ndash; War of the Austrian Succession: Austria and [[Sardinia]] defeat a Franco-Spanish army at the [[Battle of Piacenza]]. *[[1755]] &ndash; [[French and Indian War]]: The [[Military history of France|French]] surrender [[Fort Beauséjour]] to the British, leading to the expulsion of the [[Acadians]]. *[[1774]] &ndash; Foundation of [[Harrodsburg, Kentucky]]. *[[1779]] &ndash; Spain declares war on the Kingdom of Great Britain, and the [[Great Siege of Gibraltar]] begins. *[[1795]] &ndash; [[French Revolutionary Wars]]: In what became known as [[Cornwallis's Retreat]], a British [[Royal Navy]] squadron led by Vice Admiral [[William Cornwallis]] strongly resists a much larger [[French Navy]] force and withdraws largely intact, setting up the French Navy defeat at the [[Battle of Groix]] six days later. *[[1811]] &ndash; Survivors of an attack the previous day by [[Tla-o-qui-aht First Nations|Tla-o-qui-aht]] on board the [[Pacific Fur Company]]'s ship ''[[Tonquin (1807)|Tonquin]]'' intentionally detonate a powder magazine on the ship, [[Battle of Woody Point|destroying it]] and killing about 100 attackers.<ref>{{Cite encyclopedia |title=Tonquin |url=https://www.thecanadianencyclopedia.ca/en/article/tonquin/ |last=Gough |first=Barry M. |language=en |encyclopedia=The Canadian Encyclopedia |publisher=[[Historica Canada]] |access-date=2018-09-06}}</ref> *[[1815]] &ndash; [[Battle of Ligny]] and [[Battle of Quatre Bras]], two days before the [[Battle of Waterloo]]. *[[1836]] &ndash; The formation of the [[London Working Men's Association]] gives rise to the [[Chartism|Chartist Movement]]. *[[1846]] &ndash; The [[Papal conclave, 1846|Papal conclave of 1846]] elects [[Pope Pius IX]], beginning the longest reign in the history of the papacy. *[[1858]] &ndash; [[Abraham Lincoln]] delivers his ''[[Lincoln's House Divided Speech|House Divided]]'' speech in [[Springfield, Illinois]]. * 1858 &ndash; The Battle of Morar takes place during the [[Indian Mutiny]]. *[[1871]] &ndash; The [[Universities Tests Act 1871|University Tests Act]] allows students to enter the Universities of [[University of Oxford|Oxford]], [[University of Cambridge|Cambridge]] and [[Durham University|Durham]] without religious tests (except for those intending to study [[theology]]). *[[1883]] &ndash; The [[Victoria Hall stampede|Victoria Hall theatre panic]] in [[Sunderland, Tyne and Wear|Sunderland]], England kills 183 children. *[[1884]] &ndash; The first purpose-built roller coaster, [[LaMarcus Adna Thompson]]'s "[[Switchback Railway]]", opens in New York's [[Coney Island]] amusement park. *[[1897]] &ndash; A treaty annexing the [[Republic of Hawaii]] to the United States is signed; the Republic would not be dissolved until a year later. *[[1903]] &ndash; The [[Ford Motor Company]] is incorporated. * 1903 &ndash; [[Roald Amundsen]] commences the first east-west navigation of the [[Northwest Passage]], leaving [[Oslo]], Norway. *[[1904]] &ndash; [[Eugen Schauman]] assassinates [[Nikolay Bobrikov]], [[Governor-General of Finland]]. * 1904 &ndash; Irish author [[James Joyce]] begins a relationship with [[Nora Barnacle]] and subsequently uses the date to set the actions for his novel ''[[Ulysses (novel)|Ulysses]]''; this date is now traditionally called "[[Bloomsday]]". *[[1911]] &ndash; [[IBM]] founded as the Computing-Tabulating-Recording Company in [[Endicott, New York]]. *[[1922]] &ndash; General election in the [[Irish Free State]]: The pro-Treaty [[History of Sinn Féin|Sinn Féin]] win a large majority. *[[1925]] &ndash; The most famous [[Young Pioneer]] camp of the [[Soviet Union]], [[Artek (camp)|Artek]], is established. *[[1930]] &ndash; [[Sovnarkom]] establishes [[decree time]] in the USSR. *[[1933]] &ndash; The [[National Industrial Recovery Act]] is passed in the United States, allowing businesses to avoid [[antitrust]] prosecution if they established voluntary wage, price, and working condition regulations on an industry-wide basis. Large portions of the law are later declared [[A.L.A. Schechter Poultry Corp. v. United States|unconstitutional]]. *[[1940]] &ndash; [[World War II]]: Marshal [[Henri Philippe Pétain]] becomes Chief of State of [[Vichy France]] (''Chef de l'État Français''). * 1940 &ndash; A [[Communist]] government is installed in [[Lithuania]]. *[[1944]] &ndash; At age 14, [[George Stinney|George Junius Stinney, Jr.]] becomes the youngest person executed in the United States in the 20th century. *[[1948]] &ndash; Members of the [[Malayan Communist Party]] kill three British plantation managers in [[Sungai Siput]]; in response, [[British Malaya]] declares [[Malayan Emergency|a state of emergency]]. *[[1955]] &ndash; In a futile effort to topple Argentine President [[Juan Perón]], rogue aircraft pilots of the [[Argentine Navy]] [[Bombing of Plaza de Mayo|drop several bombs]] upon an unarmed crowd demonstrating in favor of Perón in [[Buenos Aires]], killing 364 and injuring at least 800. At the same time on the ground, some soldiers attempt to stage a coup but are suppressed by loyal forces. *[[1958]] &ndash; [[Imre Nagy]], [[Pál Maléter]] and other leaders of the 1956 [[Hungarian Revolution of 1956|Hungarian Uprising]] are executed. *[[1961]] &ndash; [[Rudolf Nureyev]] defects from the Soviet Union. *[[1963]] &ndash; Soviet Space Program: ''[[Vostok 6]]'' Mission: [[Cosmonaut]] [[Valentina Tereshkova]] becomes the first woman in space. *[[1972]] &ndash; The largest single-site hydroelectric power project in Canada is inaugurated at [[Churchill Falls Generating Station]]. *[[1976]] &ndash; [[Soweto uprising]]: A non-violent march by 15,000 students in [[Soweto]], South Africa turns into days of rioting when police open fire on the crowd. *[[1977]] &ndash; [[Oracle Corporation]] is incorporated in [[Redwood Shores, California]], as Software Development Laboratories (SDL) by [[Larry Ellison]], [[Bob Miner]] and [[Ed Oates]]. *[[1981]] &ndash; U.S. President [[Ronald Reagan]] awards the [[Congressional Gold Medal]] to [[Kenneth D. Taylor|Ken Taylor]], Canada's former ambassador to [[Iran]], for helping six Americans escape from Iran during the [[Iran hostage crisis|hostage crisis of 1979-81]]; he is the first foreign citizen bestowed the honor. *[[1989]] &ndash; [[Revolutions of 1989]]: [[Imre Nagy]], the former Hungarian [[Prime Minister of Hungary|Prime Minister]], is reburied in [[Budapest]] following the collapse of Communism in Hungary. *[[1997]] &ndash; [[Daïat Labguer (M'sila) massacre]] in [[Algeria]]: Fifty people die. *[[2000]] &ndash; [[Israel]] complies with [[United Nations Security Council Resolution 425]] 22 years after its issuance, which calls on Israel to completely withdraw from [[Lebanon]]. Israel does so, except the disputed [[Shebaa farms]]. *[[2010]] &ndash; [[Bhutan]] becomes the first country to institute a [[Tobacco Control Act of Bhutan 2010|total ban on tobacco]]. *[[2012]] &ndash; China successfully launches its [[Shenzhou 9]] spacecraft, carrying three astronauts, including the first female Chinese astronaut [[Liu Yang (astronaut)|Liu Yang]], to the [[Tiangong-1]] orbital module. * 2012 &ndash; The [[United States Air Force]]'s robotic [[Boeing X-37B]] [[spaceplane]] returns to Earth after a [[USA-226|classified 469-day orbital mission]]. *[[2013]] &ndash; A multi-day [[2013 North India floods|cloudburst]] centered on the North Indian state of [[Uttarakhand]] caused devastating floods and landslides becoming the country's worst natural disaster since the 2004 tsunami. *[[2016]] &ndash; [[Shanghai Disneyland Park]], the first Disney Park in Mainland China opens to the public.
