{{pizza}}
[[File:Ubuntu 10.10 Countdown Party at Taipei 101 BobChao 3.jpg|thumb|upright|Pizzas at a pizza party]]
A '''pizza party''' is a social gathering at which [[pizza]] is served.<ref>{{cite journal|title=The pizza party|journal=Teaching Children Mathematics|date=March 2016|volume=22|issue=7|pages=398–400|jstor=10.5951/teacchilmath.22.7.0398}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Saltiel|first1=Jennifer|title=How to Host a Make-Your-Own Pizza Party|url=http://www.goodhousekeeping.com/food-recipes/party-ideas/a17153/kids-party-pizza-may07/|accessdate=9 August 2016|work=[[Good Housekeeping]]|date=25 April 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|last1=Chase|first1=Chris|title=Here's Roger Federer housing some pizza with ballkids|url=http://ftw.usatoday.com/2015/11/roger-federer-wins-basel-swiss-open-pizza-party-ball-kids-tradition-why|accessdate=8 August 2016|work=[[USA Today]]|date=1 November 2015}}</ref>

Typically, a pizza that is 10 to 14 inches wide will feed two people.<ref name=awesome>Knudson, Pamela.  [http://www.grandforksherald.com/accent/food/3933383-how-throw-awesome-personal-pizza-party "How to throw an awesome personal pizza party"], ''[[Grand Forks Herald]]'' (January 27, 2016).</ref>  Since pizzas can include a very wide variety of toppings, one particular type of pizza party allows the party-goers to create their own custom-made pizza, using a selection of ingredients from among the toppings provided by the party's host.<ref name=awesome />

When a pizza party does not include any custom-made pizzas, and the particular preferences of the guests are unknown, it is common to include at least one plain cheese-only or vegetable-only pizza for people who are averse to meats or other available toppings.<ref>Hulin, Belinda.  ''[https://books.google.com/books?id=pZAv_kYu-9UC&pg=PA13 The Everything Pizza Cookbook: 300 Crowd-Pleasing Slices of Heaven]'', p. 13 (Everything Books, 2007).</ref>

