{{Infobox film festival | name = VIVA Film Festival | logo = File:Viva.film.festival.2017.jpg | logo_caption = Official logo | image = | image_size = | caption = | founded = {{start date and age|2015}} | number = | location = [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]] | language = International | website = {{URL|http://www.vivaba.com/}} }}
The '''VIVA Film Festival''' is an annual [[documentary film|documentary]] [[film festival]] that is based in [[Sarajevo]], [[Bosnia and Herzegovina]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://vivaba.com/|title=About|publisher=official website}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/magazin/film-tv/dodjelom-nagrada-zatvoren-viva-film-festival-u-sarajevu/160605062|title=Dodjelom nagrada zatvoren VIVA film festival u Sarajevu|publisher=klix.ba}}</ref> The festival showcases international films with ecological, religious and touristic themes, as well as youth-made films. <ref>{{cite web|url=http://ba.n1info.com/a204385/Showbiz/Showbiz-vesti/Scena-Pocinje-Viva-Film-Festival-u-Sarajevu.html|title=Scena: Počinje Viva Film Festival u Sarajevu|publisher=N1 Televizija}}</ref> It was established by an international team of film professionals, [[environmentalists]], diplomats, religious leaders and scholars that includes former [[List of Vice Presidents of the United States|US Vice President]] [[Al Gore]] (current festival Vice Chairman), Bosnian archeologist [[Semir Osmanagić]], Austrian diplomat currently serving as the [[High Representative for Bosnia and Herzegovina]] [[Valentin Inzko]] and others, with the purpose of promoting inter-religious dialogue, the preservation of the environment and [[ecotourism]]. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.klix.ba/magazin/film-tv/veni-vidi-viva-u-sarajevu-svecano-otvoren-drugi-viva-film-festival/160602116|title=Veni vidi VIVA: U Sarajevu svečano otvoren drugi VIVA film festival|publisher=klix.ba}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://visoko.co.ba/intervju-sa-ratkom-orozovicem-veni-vidi-viva-fest/|title=Intervju sa Ratkom Orozovićem – Veni Vidi Viva Fest|publisher=visoko.co.ba}}</ref> <ref>{{cite web|url=http://vivaba.com/?page_id=6933|title=VIVA Festival Team|publisher=official website}}</ref>
==Format==
The festival is composed of five competition programs: Grand Prix, Ecology, Religion, Tourism and Youth-directed. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.vecernji.ba/kultura/dunovic-otvorio-viva-film-festival-1088989|title=Dunović otvorio VIVA film festival |publisher=vecernji.ba}}</ref> It is based in Sarajevo, where the centre piece events, projections and award ceremonies are held, but also travels to cities and towns across Bosnia and Herzegovina. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bljesak.info/kultura/film-tv/sarajevo-38-premijera-na-ovogodisnjem-viva-festivalu/208317|title=Sarajevo: 38 premijera na ovogodišnjem VIVA festivali.|publisher=vecernji.ba}}</ref> Each town has its own management departement and they are all interlinked. Heads of the various management departements sit in the festival's managing council. Each year's competition selection includes more than 100 films from over 45 countries that tackle the issues of inter-religious dialogue, environmentalism and ecotourism. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oslobodjenje.ba/o2/kultura/film/treci-viva-festival-filmovi-s-porukom-za-bolje-sutra|title=Treći VIVA festival: Filmovi s porukom za bolje sutra|publisher=oslobodjenje.ba}}</ref> A panel of filmmakers, religious and community leaders, writers and human rights advocates judges the entries, based both on their cinematic value and on their message, deciding on the three best films from each program. <ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.oslobodjenje.ba/o2/kultura/film/treci-viva-festival-filmovi-s-porukom-za-bolje-sutra|title=Treći VIVA festival: Filmovi s porukom za bolje sutra|publisher=oslobodjenje.ba}}</ref>
